				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">FT cap is different from +mana cap.
<br />

<br />
The mana cap is the total amount of additional mana you can get from spells, aa's, etc.  I dont think enchanters come close to hitting it but with the new abilities some wizards discovered it when they should have been receiving x amount of mana from their buffs but were only getting y.
<br />

<br />
I dont know the exact number, I'm sure graffes would have some info regarding it.
<br />

<br />
Regarding the changes for us, the changes to the poison based line of spells for less tash aggro, I like the idea.  In regards to charming solution, I think its a catch-22.  We can keep what we have now and be able to use charm on mobs 6 levels lower than us and keep their full power in zones other than oow, or we can accept the oow nerf across the entier game and then charm anything and everything in any zone.
<br />

<br />
On one hand, I like the sound of it, on the other, I dont.  Simply because I enjoy the risk of having the all powerful pet in out of the reac places that can turn me into a smear stain if I mess up.
<br />

<br />
Guess I will just wait and see.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=450192" target="_blank" class="postlink">Edarila Aethan`Dor</a> | <a href="http://www.therunes.net" target="_blank" class="postlink">Bedazzler</a> | <a href="http://www.tenacityguild.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tenacity</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1178832" target="_blank" class="postlink">---Demipint Edslave</a> | <a href="http://www.eqdiva.net" target="_blank" class="postlink">---Prelate</a> | <a href="http://www.tenacityguild.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tenacity</a>
<br />

<br />
