			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm nerf math.
<br />

<br />
The existing charm nerf drops mob hits to about 260, depending on the mob's level.
<br />

<br />
Their full damage is between 700 and 1200, depending on the zone.
<br />

<br />
Lets assume the haste spells are 100%, and make the pet dual-wield.  The mob dual wields half the time.
<br />

<br />
260 * 2 * 1.5 = 780.
<br />

<br />
If this is true, then a 780 hitting mob charmed will do identical DPS when charmed, hitting for 260 max, dual-wielding 50% of the time, and attacking twice as often. <span style="font-style: italic">edit: paragraph reworded</span>
<br />

<br />
A 260 hitting pet does about 100 DPS unhasted on other mobs of it's type.
<br />

<br />
120 * 2 * 1.5 = 360 DPS.
<br />

<br />
A table of various possiblities, for a 1000 hitting L 68 mob that charms to a max hit of 260:
<br />

<br />
Current: 100 DPS, or -74% DPS when charmed
<br />
70%H:  170 DPS, or -56% DPS when charmed
<br />
100%H: 200 DPS, or -48% DPS when charmed
<br />
70%H+DW: 255 DPS, or -33% DPS when charmed
<br />
100%H+DW: 300 DPS, or -22% DPS when charmed
<br />

<br />
Notice how they start approaching "1% slow and no gearing charmed pets" at the high end.
<br />

<br />
However, personally I expect 70% haste, which places enchanter charm DPS at about bard-melee levels.
<br />

<br />
I'd expect any strategic use of charm outside of scripted events to go away.  RZtW, AD, HoHa dragon, Tipt/Vxed, etc.
<br />

<br />
Another way of looking at it:  Suppose you are using charm extravagantly.  Say, LDoN hard hasted+DW pet, or Tipt hasted+DW pet with item haste gear on them.
<br />

<br />
And now you use the new charm.
<br />

<br />
LDoN hard: (100% item+spell haste, DWing)
<br />
950 max hit -&gt; 245 max hit.
<br />
900 DPS -&gt; ~ 232 DPS (best case) or 155 DPS (no DW in new charm)
<br />

<br />
Tipt: (see above)
<br />
1100 max hit -&gt; 245 max hit.
<br />
1200 DPS -&gt; 300 DPS (best case) or 200 DPS (no DW in new charm)
<br />

<br />
Personally, if SOE would address the enchanter:tank mitigation ratio (otherwise known as, ker-splat on aggro), <span style="font-weight: bold">and</span> give us at least 1 1.5 casting time and 1 1.0 casting time active defensive spells on seperate timers that work up the xp-level-cap of 73, <span style="font-weight: bold">and</span> actually deliver on the 'remove charm immunities' at the same time as the charm nerf, <span style="font-weight: bold">and</span> deal with the fact that charm is used strategically in a number of progression events for massive-DPS which this nerf is removing, <span style="font-weight: bold">and</span> fix the mez hard-caps/stacking issues, <span style="font-weight: bold">and</span> make charmed mobs auto-DW and 70%+ haste with the L 69 charm spell, <span style="font-weight: bold">and</span> they repealed the 33% xp nerf on charmed pets, <span style="font-weight: bold">then</span> I'd say good job.
<br />

<br />
I doubt they'll go that far.  They'll probably implement exactly what they are promising, which is:
<br />

<br />
Almost, but not quite, viable charm in OOW and beyond.  170 DPS pets that do 500 DPS when charm breaks.  Because regular adds are not viable in challenging content, charm still won't be.  It will be harder to reverse-charm.
<br />

<br />
The same charm code added to all existing charmable mobs in EQ.  With the same results.
<br />

<br />
No new mobs flagged charmable (they promised "they could make more mobs charmable", which is the same thing they said when OOW was released.  Notice the complete lack of new charmable mobs outside of OOW.) for at least a few expansions.
<br />

<br />
The new WoM with a 2.0 casting time, L 70 cap.
<br />

<br />
After all, this is what they said they where going to do.
<br />

<br />
I apologize to any SOE devs if this looks hostile.  But I haven't been admiring how you balanced and delt with charm.  It was pretty easy to do the math showing that charm wasn't worth using after the OOW nerf (an unbuffed charmed pet generated the same XP-over-time as an animation, and hasting/DWing a pet in challenging content -- notice how people build <span style="font-weight: bold">groups</span> around buffed pets in Tipt?).  So I'm not feeling charitable.
<br />

<br />
I'm assuming you'll do exactly what you described.  And I don't find it impressive.  You do realize that of all the classes, enchanters are the only one that recieve a nerf in this re-invisioning?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
