			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">"Beastlords
<br />

<br />
We will add at least one new slow spell for you which has an innate resistance mod built in so that it lands more often.  This will help you perform the role of slower in your groups, since you don't have access to the powerful resistance lowering spells of other slowing classes."
<br />

<br />
I was liking the direction this was going until I read that. 
<br />

<br />
New WoM wuwuw! 
<br />

<br />
Charm changes? Still seems like Sony dont know how to charm, nor why we do it. Charm adds a risk for a reward, not a risk for a morsel. Increase charm duration of you want to to be integral. Make it worth the considerable effort and loss of the ability to go to the toilet... The pets hit like girls (um weak girls who cant hit), until they break, and are then a MASSIVE problem.
<br />

<br />
Emergency CC became extinct around the time we were 1 round bait.
<br />

<br />
Improving soloing for everyone. Bout time.
<br />

<br />
Mana drain changes. So now i have to mem 3 or 4 spells to get a decent return? Will my non-tap drain spells be actually able to completely drain a mob?
<br />

<br />
But Slow improvements for BSTs? Soooo, now chanters can bring a charmed pet to a group. That it? Anything else? No CC improvements (apart from WoM2, which will be russian roulette anyway). What about those who dont like to charm?
<br />

<br />
We are invited to groups for our role as slower. That is the number 1 consideration when a chanter is chosen. The group must have a slower, healer and tank. Which slower you choose depends on what else they can bring (except for high MR zones like KodTaz. Any slower but a chanter plz). The BST gives risk free DPs and nice mana regen, and burst regen of Paragon (which chanters cant) which has saved groups many times. Shaman, buffs and healz.
<br />

<br />
CC is long gone as a criteria for selecting chanters. Having something like a -50MR, 18 second mezz, with a 2 minute recast would make people sit up and take notice of our CC ability again. We could lock down 1 mob effectively, tash and remezz. You know, our job... If 2 adds, we lock down one, deal with the other. Things can still go pear shaped easy, but at least the skilled chanter would have a chance. We could do our damn job again! We need the tools to be able to survive the Add. We mezz. We love mezzing. We like charming, but mezzing... /drool...
<br />

<br />
Currently I hate mezzing. I hate dieing while trying to do my job. It's embarassing, frustrating and just plain not fun...
<br />

<br />
Ergo, I play EQ2.
<br />

<br />
I do think there are steps being taken in the right direction here. For 1, communication. It seems there has actually been some listening going on. Also, it seems that Sony will attempt to address the stagnation of EQ (no, expansions dont help when your class is simply not fun), by fixing things. doing stuff. Identifying and adressing issues.
<br />

<br />
Course, Even though I played for 15 months, I am well used to Sony promising and not delivering. I will wait and see.
<br />

<br />
It does make me wanna jump on EQ1 tonight though. It gives me hope Sony have decided to stop ignoring the state of EQ and may actually have a future, not a slow, painful death...
<br />

<br />
Lonwen
<br />
70 chanter</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
