				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Wow, I'm glad I don't work for SoE.  People really do like to bitch a lot.
<br />

<br />
I've read a lot of places where enchanters were *begging* for reduction in agro from tash, and pleading for an item that would reduce it.  Now SoE is talking about reducing it and people start bitching.
<br />

<br />
SoE fixes ToT and people bitch.  How long have enchanters been complaining about this?  How often do NPCs use all their mana?  I don't think it will be a problem if we only get the mana an NPC has left.
<br />

<br />
And charm?  It remains to be seen, but they realize there is a problem and are trying to address it.  I'll wait to see how the numbers work out, but I'm hopeful.  Let's not start bitching before we know what's going to happen.  If you are concerned, go the our official message board and give some suggestions.  But I like the idea of a buff built-in to the charm.  It will basically weaken the mobs when charm wears off.  Isn't that fixing something we were asking for?  
<br />

<br />
Granted, their track record isn't the best, but many people seem to be jumping to conclusions.  These sound like some great changes.
<br />

