<br />

<br />
What I don't get is the statement about mobs that are immune to spells now will mitigate it instead. Exactly what does a mitigated mez mean? Or were they not even including that?  A random duration mez just doesn't cut it, I need to know when mez wears off because we don't let them break, we keep them mezed. A mitigated charm? A mitigated stun? I'm clueless here what they mean.
<br />

<br />
Taking the level cap off fear is nice and all, but what about all our spells? Mez, charm, stun, etc (actually stun bugs me most).
<br />

<br />
Removing agro from tash is great, but what about a resisted slow? That is the single most agro thing I can do (of course, I probably will not be slowing much anyway per the above).
<br />

<br />
Maybe if you are a 10 k hp unbuffed enchanter you have a different view on the game than the rest of us.  But I'm a 70 enchanter who has played my character devotedly for 4 years, I just don't get this at all, and am sadly afraid its the end of my character.
<br />

<br />
We're back to a statement I haven't dragged out in nearly 2 years. Does anybody who is responsible for enchanters at Sony have a clue what the life of an average enchanter is like?  I really don't get it, how can they be this far off ALL the time?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
